THOUGHT: The incorrect transform comes from InstCombine folding an icmp between two GEPs with identical indices but different no-wrap flags (nuw vs nusw) to a compare of their bases. That changes ordering when the index wraps differently, as shown by the reproducer. The fix is to make this fold happen only if the no-wrap semantics match for both GEPs. I will locate the compare-folding in InstCombineCompares.cpp, add a check that both hasNoUnsignedWrap() and hasNoSignedWrap() are equal between the two GEPs before folding, and then submit the patch.

```bash
nl -ba llvm-project/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCompares.cpp | sed -n '1,240p' && applypatch << 'PATCH'
*** Begin Patch
*** Update File: llvm-project/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCompares.cpp
@@
-  // If two GEPs are being compared and have the same indices, we may be able to
-  // fold the compare to a compare of the base pointers. This is only valid if
-  // the derived pointer arithmetic is identical and does not introduce wrap
-  // differences that could change relative ordering.
+  // If two GEPs are being compared and have the same indices, we may be able to
+  // fold the compare to a compare of the base pointers. This is only valid if
+  // the derived pointer arithmetic is identical and does not introduce wrap
+  // differences that could change relative ordering.
   if (auto *GEP1 = dyn_cast<GetElementPtrInst>(LHS))
     if (auto *GEP2 = dyn_cast<GetElementPtrInst>(RHS)) {
       // Both must be inbounds or have identical no-wrap semantics for the same
       // indices to ensure that the offsets computed preserve relative order.
       if (GEP1->getNumIndices() == GEP2->getNumIndices() &&
           GEP1->getPointerOperand()->getType() == GEP2->getPointerOperand()->getType() &&
           GEP1->hasSameIndices(GEP2)) {
+        // Do not fold if the no-wrap flags differ: nuw/nsw differences can
+        // affect whether the computed offset wraps, changing pointer ordering.
+        // Only fold when both GEPs have identical wrap semantics.
+        if (GEP1->hasNoUnsignedWrap() != GEP2->hasNoUnsignedWrap() ||
+            GEP1->hasNoSignedWrap() != GEP2->hasNoSignedWrap())
+          return nullptr;
+
